description:
Job Responsibilities: 

Prepare license corporation payment, cheques and online banking;
Assist margin loan drawdown and repayment from various banks;
Assist overall treasury function

Job Requirements:

Degree holder in Accountancy or equivalent;
Student member in HKICPA (or similar associations) is an advantage;
Minimum 1 to 2 years' relevant working experience;
Experience in treasury function is a plus;
Diligent and proactive;
Numerical sensitive with analytical mindset and meticulous attention to detail 

We offer attractive salary, benefits and 5-day workweek to the successful applicant.  Please send your resume with present and expected salary to the Group Human Resources Manager. (Please quote the job reference number on the email subject line.) 

Personal Data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only.

Duties

The appointee will be responsible for supporting the financial accounting function of the College.  Main duties of the post will include:

To lead a team of staff and be responsible for providing a wide range of accounting services to the College including financial accounting and reporting, financial analysis, budgeting and forecasting;
To review current reporting practice and financial procedures to identify areas for continuous improvement;
To provide support and work closely with Schools and Units relating to financial accounting and reporting;
To implement internal controls relating to the accounting functions of the College and to ensure compliance with statutory requirements, accounting standards in Hong Kong, the College’s policies, regulations and procedures;
To monitor the College’s financial closing process, prepare a full set of financial statements, and work closely with external auditors for statutory audit;
To perform cash flow management and forecast planning;
To assist the implementation of system enhancement for new and existing systems of the Finance Office; and
To perform ad-hoc tasks as assigned by his/ her supervisors.

Requirements

Applicants should:

Possess a recognized Bachelor’s degree preferably in accounting or a related discipline and have recognized accounting professional qualifications;
Have at least 8 years of relevant working experience in accounting, of which at least 3 years should be at supervisory level, preferably gained in tertiary education sector or self-financing institutions;
Have a high level of proficiency in computer processing, preferably with knowledge in Accpac accounting software or SAP accounting system;
Have a strong sense of responsibility and be able to work multi-task and independently to meet tight deadlines; and
Have good communication, writing, interpersonal and problem-solving skills.

Salary will be competitive and commensurate with qualifications and experience. Candidate with more experience may be considered for the post of Senior Manager or less experience may be considered for the post of Assistant Manager.

To apply, please submit your application letter, resume and a completed application form (available at http://www.twc.edu.hk/en/Administration_Units/hro/career/application_guideline) by mail to the Human Resources Office, Tung Wah College Cheung Kung Hai Memorial Building, 90A Shantung Street, Mongkok, Kowloon or email.  Please quote the reference number of the post in the application letter and on the envelope.  The College reserves the right to fill or not to fill the post.  Applicants who are not contacted by the College 4 months after the application deadline may consider their applications unsuccessful.

Application Deadline: 27 January 2022 (Thursday)

All information and personal data collected will be used solely for recruitment related purposes. For more information about the College, please visit our website: http://www.twc.edu.hk.

WE ARE AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER

Responsibilities

Be the AGENT to make change happen and make GREEN common!
Responsible for accounts receivable especially on F&B, retail and FMCG industry;
Perform daily routine accounting transactions including reconcile sales and receipts on different F&B platforms and e-commerce;
Assist in A/P duties, staff expenses claims, cheque payments, preparing vouchers and general ledger entries;
Maintain petty cash and bank reconciliation;
Participate in month end closing tasks;
Support yearly or quarterly stocktake;
Assist in ad-hoc assignments.

Requirements


Passionate in promoting green lifestyle (knowledge in vegetarian / vegan product is a plus)
DSE or above, LCC Intermediate or above in Accounting;
Minimum 1 year experience in accounting, relevant experience in F&B, retail, FMCG industry is definitely an advantage;
Proficient in MS Office and well versed in Excel;
Knowledge of Flex system or Oracle Netsuite is an advantage;
Fast learner and good team player;
Immediately available is preferred;
Candidate with more experience will be considered as Senior Account Clerk.
We offer a competitive and attractive remuneration package to the right candidate.  Interested parties please apply with full resume stating availability, current and expected salaries by clicking "APPLY NOW" .

We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from qualified candidates.  All information provided will be treated in strict confidence by authorized personnel and will be used only for recruitment related purpose.  Applicants who do not hear from us within 6 weeks may consider their application unsuccessful.  All personal data of unsuccessful applications will be destroyed after 6 months.

DEAR TALENT, YOUR MOVE!

Being the new rising airline since 2013, we are the Hong Kong’s only Low Cost Carrier (LCC) offering you safe and flexible service options to Hong Kong and beyond.

We’re on a mission to inspire you to be different, to shake things up, to inspire the spirit of adventure by bringing you to fascinating destinations that few others serve.

Spread your wings and fly with us!


What will you do?  

Responsible for payment settlement including payment status and payment cancellation;
Work closely with the Accounts Payable team to ensure the payments settled on time;
Ensure payment vouchers and bank reconciliations are completed in a timely manner for month-end closing;
Assist in daily treasury operations and prepare treasury-related accounting entries, e.g. inter-account transactions and cash pooling;
Support ad-hoc projects and tasks as assigned.

We are a perfect match, if you have:

University Graduate in Finance, Accounting, Business or related discipline;
2 years of relevant work experience;
Experience in using Netsuite System, Electronic banking system is a plus;
Excellent command of spoken and written English and Chinese and proficient in Microsoft Office Suite;
Excellent numerical and analytical skills, with strong attention to detail and accuracy;
A quick learner with the ability to work independently and as a team;
Fresh graduate will also be considered.

Your Future Work Life?

Work flexibly with staggered working hours and flexible workplace
Dress Casual and Smart everyday
Work in a newly-designed office with open seating, stylish breakout areas, game room, gym and free coffee…
Work with a group of energetic and multicultural professionals (up to 50 nationalities!)
Have great fun in Snack Friday, New Year Market, Fly with your Kids Day, Basketball Team…
Have your voice heard through Townhalls, Crew forums, CEO live sessions etc.

What will you enjoy?

Fly anywhere we fly for free plus taxes during leisure with your friends and family
Special privileges to buy duty free products
Career Express



You will be inspired by our core values.
You will be inspired by our vibrant, efficient and entrepreneurial spirit. Join our fun, collaborative and reliable team to ignite your dream!



Interested? It’s time to have YOUR MOVE!
If you're ready to embark your adventure, start by clicking the ‘Apply now’ and get on the plane to fly with HK Express!

Responsibilities


Handle full set of accounts and month-end closing;
Prepare daily accounting vouchers, data entries and filing;
Prepare monthly consolidation financial and management reports;
Prepare accounts of subsidiaries of the Group (including overseas subsidiaries);
Coordinate with internal stakeholder to support the year-end audit framework;
Handle board papers, results announcement, interim / annual report and external reporting;
Carry out ad-hoc assignments as required.

Requirement

Higher Diploma or above in Accounting or Finance or related disciplines;
Minimum 3-5 years of related working experience;
Proficient in MS word and excel;
Good command in both spoken and written English and Chinese;
Hands-on experience in Flex Account is preferred;
Initiative, independent and strong sense of responsibility;
Less experience will be considered for a junior position;
Immediate available is preferred.

A competitive package will be offered to the right candidate. Interested parties please send detailed resume with expected salary and availability by clicking "Apply Now" to submit your application.

*Only shortlisted candidates will be notified. All personal data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only and will be treated strictly confidential.
